                <!--1. The internet’s History-->
                <TextView
                    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_marginTop="@dimen/padding"
                    android:text="1. The internet’s History"
                    android:textSize="@dimen/h2"
                    android:textStyle="bold" />

                <TextView
                    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:text="The internet, also called the Net, is a worldwide collection of networks that links millions of businesses, government agencies, educational institutions, and individuals. The Internet has its roots in ARPANET, a network started in 1969 to link scientific and academic researchers across the United States. In 1986, the National Science Foundation connected its huge network, called NSF net, to ARPANET, creating a configuration of complex networks and hosts that became known as the Internet. Today, more than 550 million bostcomputers connect to the Internet."
                    android:textSize="@dimen/h2"
                    android:textStyle="normal" />

                <!--2. What are the various types of the Internet connections?-->
                <TextView
                    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
